The paper presents a method for semi-supervised learning using kernel-based methods and spectral graph theory. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method is applied to classification tasks, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which is relevant to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
